  "local_port": 41022,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "The **Staff Selection Commission (SSC)** is an organization under the Government of India that conducts various examinations to recruit eligible candidates for different posts across various ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India. Here are the primary examinations and the corresponding postings under SSC:\n\n### 1. **SSC Combined Graduate Level (CGL) Examination**\nThis is one of the most popular SSC exams, targeting graduates for various Group B and Group C posts.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Assistant Audit Officer / Assistant Accounts Officer**\n- **Inspector of Income Tax/Central Excise Inspector**\n- **Assistant IAS / PCS Officer (by SSC CGL)**\n- **Inspector (Central Bureau of Investigation)**\n- **Assistant Section Officer**\n- **Commercial Tax Officer**\n- **Technical Assistant**\n- **Tax Assistant / EXE**\n- **Audit Assistant**\n- **Jr. Statistical Officer**\n\n### 2. **SSC Combined Higher Secondary Level (CHSL) Examination**\nDesigned for candidates who have completed their higher secondary education (10+2).\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Lower Division Clerk (LDC)**\n- **Data Entry Operator (DEO)**\n- **Postal Assistant / Sorting Assistant**\n- **Revenue Assistant**\n- **Court Clerk**\n\n### 3. **SSC Junior Engineer (JE) Examination**\nAimed at engineering graduates for technical roles in various government departments.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Junior Engineer (Civil, Electrical, Mechanical, etc.)**\n- **Sub-Engineer (Civil/Mechanical/Electrical)**\n\n### 4. **SSC Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS) Examination**\nFor candidates who have completed their 8th standard or equivalent.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS)**\n- **Clerk**\n- **Receptionist**\n- **Store Keeper**\n- **Data Entry Operator**\n\n### 5. **SSC Stenographer Examination**\nTargets candidates skilled in shorthand and typing.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Stenographer Grade C & D**\n  - **PMO Stenographer Grade B**\n  - **Investigation Branch Stenographer**\n  - **Judicial Stenographer**\n\n### 6. **SSC Combined Police Officer (CPO) Examination**\nRecruits candidates for various police and paramilitary positions.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Assistant Sub-Inspector (ASI) in Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs)**\n- **Sub-Inspector**\n- **Assistant Transit Munshi**\n- **Assistant Enforcement Officer**\n- **Data Entry Operator**\n\n### 7. **SSC Central Police Organization (CPO)**\nSpecifically focuses on recruitment for central police roles.\n\n**Postings Include:**\n- **Sub-Inspector (SI) in Central Police Organizations**\n- **Assistant Transit Munshi**\n- **Divisional Transport Manager**\n- **Police Station Clerk**\n\n### 8. **SSC JE (Junior Engineer) for Various Ministries**\nApart from the general JE exam, SSC also conducts specific JE exams for different ministries like Railways, Defense, etc.\n\n### 9. **SSC CEB (Combined Engineering Background) Examination**\nFocuses on engineering graduates for technical roles in government departments.\n\n### 10. **SSC Special Services Group (SSG) Officer Recruitment**\nFor specialized roles requiring specific skills and expertise.\n\n### **Additional Examinations and Postings:**\n- **SSC BD (Bookkeeper/Debit Clerk)**\n- **SSC Delhi, Bihar, etc., Regional Exams**: Tailored for specific regions with roles suited to local governance needs.\n\n### **Key Points to Remember:**\n- **Eligibility:** Varies based on the examination and the post. Common criteria include educational qualifications, age limits, and sometimes specific skill sets.\n- **Frequency:** Most SSC exams are conducted annually, but some may have different schedules.\n- **Application Process:** Typically conducted online through the official SSC website ([ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in)).\n\n### **Preparation Tips:**\n- **Understand the Exam Pattern:** Each exam has its own structure regarding sections, question types, and marking schemes.\n- **Syllabus Coverage:** Thoroughly cover the syllabus outlined in the official notification.\n- **Regular Practice:** Engage in mock tests and practice papers to enhance speed and accuracy.\n- **Stay Updated:** Keep an eye on official announcements for notifications, dates, and any changes in exam patterns.\n\nFor detailed information on each examination, including notifications, syllabi, exam patterns, and application procedures, visit the [official SSC website](https://ssc.nic.in).",
